  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:DetailedGuide/65695</id>
    <published>2013-01-11T15:45:26+00:00</published>
    <updated>2013-01-11T15:45:26+00:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/transport-statistics-notes-and-guidance-disabled-parking-badges"/>
    <title>Transport Statistics notes and guidance: Disabled Parking Badges</title>
    <category>Detailed guidance</category>
    <summary></summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This section provides technical information, notes and guidance and pre-release access relating to &lt;a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-transport/series/disabled-parking-badges-statistics"&gt;disabled parking badges statistics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="technical-information"&gt;Technical information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These statistics present information on parking badges for disabled people in England (“Blue Badges”), including numbers of valid badges, applications and medical assessments. Blue Badges remain valid for three years so figures include rolling totals for badges on issue. The data are derived from the Department’s annual survey of local authorities issuing Blue Badges.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="user-feedback-request"&gt;User feedback request&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you have any comments or queries about our statistics please let us know by completing the short &lt;a rel="external" href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/KX3YPNH"&gt;feedback form&lt;/a&gt; or by using the contact details below. We are keen to learn more about our users’ needs and experiences, to help us improve the usefulness of our statistics where possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="blue-badge-statistics-beyond-2012"&gt;Blue Badge Statistics beyond 2012&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Blue Badge Improvement Service (BBIS) is a new service that has been available to all local authorities in England since 1 January 2012. It provides a number of core services, including a central database of all Blue Badges on issue. The introduction of BBIS has implications for the future collection of Blue Badge statistics. Further information is available below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;section class="attachment embedded" id="attachment_70755"&gt;&lt;div class="attachment-thumb"&gt;
    &lt;a href="/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/49677/blue-badge-stats-from-2012-final.pdf" aria-describedby="attachment-70755-accessibility-help" class="thumbnail"&gt;
